node.text: Everyone who knows me knows Cobblermania and how much I love her (yes, my biz is a she!). Many also know all the dues I have paid and sacrifices I have made. They were worth it (in hindsight! IJS LOL) and I am doing what I love -  Growing a stable family business and a community of amazingly diverse and loyal cobblermaniacs (many of whom have become lifelong friends). Today, I am taking the time to say Thank You to one and all. I love you and I would not be here without you. Sincerely Shae!!!💞

Image may contain: text that says 'skullgummi Hey guys, you want to try something thats not overwhelmingly sweet yet flavorful you should try out cobblermania's cobblers. Best thing ever shae bakes them fresh (and they certainly taste fresh) and sells them at the torrance farmers market sat mornings at Wilson's park. Due to corona not selling there currently but they'll be back, they are selling at goldenbird in LA. Cobbler tastes like jesus made it with his bare hands trust me you will not regret'

node.text: Just saw this post. She and her boyfriend have repeatedly picked up to go cobblers (at Golden Bird, where I bake ALL Cobblermania cobblers) during Covid-19. I love love love my biz and happy cobblermaniacs!!!! Do something you love and, as one of my beloved mentors always says, do it well!!!! @originaltorrancefarmersmarket
